NSA whistleblower Edward Snowden did a sit down with American mainstream media for the first time last week and a clip is now online.

In the interview set to air on Wednesday night, NBC Nightly News anchor Brian Williams speaks to the former NSA contractor who leaked classified information about the U.S.'s surveillance a year ago.

Mr Williams travelled to Moscow, Russia, where Mr Snowden holds temporary asylum since last year, and spent several hours quizzing him.

