The exclusive interview, to be aired as an hour-long NBC special, is the latest media appearance by Mr Snowden, following a videolink speech at the South by Southwest Interactive Festival, a TED Conference in March and an interview in Vanity Fair's May issue.

Also appearing on the NBC special is Glenn Greenwald, the Pulitzer prize winning journalist who broke the NSA surveillance story in the Guardian.

Snowden’s interview comes after the House moved the U.S. closer to ending theNSA's bulk collection of Americans' phone records last Thursday.

It is the most significant demonstration to date of Snowden's impact on the debate over privacy versus security.

But the final version of the legislation, ‘watered down’ in the words of one supporter, also showed the limits of that impact.   

